text: Jake Lilley (born 20 July 1993) is an Australian competitive sailor. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, in the men's Finn class. He came eighth overall and participated in the medal race. In December 2019 Jake Lilley achieved 5th in the Finn Gold Cup (World Championships) at Royal Brighton Yacht Club in Melbourne and qualified Australia's entry position for the Finn Class to compete in 2020 Tokyo Summer Olympics ==References== ==External links== * Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Australian male sailors (sport) Category:Olympic sailors of Australia Category:Sailors at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Finn
